## HashSet.from() method

Creates a new, shallow-copied hash set instance from an iterable object.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
static from<E>(iterable?: Iterable<E>): HashSet<E>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  iterable | Iterable&lt;E&gt; | If an iterable object is passed, all of its elements will be added to the hash set. If you don't specify this parameter, or its value is <code>null</code>, the hash set is empty. |

<b>Returns:</b>

[HashSet](./calcium.hashset.md)<!-- -->&lt;E&gt;
